  "Wood_name": "Wood",
  "Wood_desc": "Commonly harvested from forest dungeons, but found on almost every isle. There are as many kinds of trees out there as there are islands in the sky, but many are similar, and wood is central to most Central Kingdom industries.",
  "Stone_name": "Stone",
  "Stone_desc": "Harvested from more barren islands and dungeons. Stones from sky islands quickly lose their bouyancy after quarrying, but are essential for larger structures.",
  "Metal_name": "Metal",
  "Metal_desc": "Most commonly found in volcanic class dungeons. Various kinds of ore are found on sky islands, often smelted into usable and pure metals that in turn can be forged into structural supports and tools.",
  "PlanktonBubzilby_name": "Bubzilby",
  "PlanktonBubzilby_desc": "Fat, jiggly, and surprisingly heavy. Often leaves behind seedpods. Some people like to drink its gooey sweat for a quick boost of energy.",
  "PlanktonBobbler_name": "Bobbler",
  "PlanktonBobbler_desc": "Sheds crunchy, watery leaves on an almost daily basis. Make sure to expose the leaves to cold for a maximum of crunch.",
  "PlanktonCrackler_name": "Crackler",
  "PlanktonCrackler_desc": "Place over a jar and squeeze regularly lest it become bloated and self important. A useful if somewhat loud plankton to have around.",
  "PlanktonSpengler_name": "Spengler",
  "PlanktonSpengler_desc": "A quiet thing that occasionally makes a loud peeping noise. Typically leaves large, heavy egg like objects full of something suspiciously similar to chocolate. Most won't know the difference.",
  "PlanktonSpartkler_name": "Spartkler",
  "PlanktonSpartkler_desc": "A glimmering creature that lights up the pen at night. Extrudes a thick, meaty lump every now and again that can be butchered for a modest cut of meat.",
  "PlanktonTwenger_name": "Twenger",
  "PlanktonTwenger_desc": "Covers itself with salt as a defence mechanism to protect itself from predators. Useful source of that substance though removing the coating can be time consuming.",
  "PlanktonWiffafler_name": "Wiffafler",
  "PlanktonWiffafler_desc": "A fragrant thing that leaves a powder of dust wherever it goes. Make sure to frequently pat it down with a feather duster and collect its leavings.",
  "PlanktonZoob_name": "Zoob",
  "PlanktonZoob_desc": "A gooey little mess of a thing. Don't be afraid to harvest its goods with a squeeze. Be prepared for a mess though?",
  "PlanktonKakabunker_name": "Kakabunkler",
  "PlanktonKakabunker_desc": "Hard shell, meaty inner core. Leaves suspicious fruits in its wake. Take care lest its bounty be eaten by its kin.",
  "PlanktonDoofler_name": "Doofler",
  "PlanktonDoofler_desc": "Produces chewy chunks of raw meat-like substance when properly tended to. Scholars ask why, you ask where the panko is.",
  "PlanktonParpler_name": "Parpler",
  "PlanktonParpler_desc": "Wherever it goes it leaves a dusty of fine spores. If left to their own devices they'll grow into fat, juice mushrooms.",
  "PlanktonRegulger_name": "Regulger",
  "PlanktonRegulger_desc": "A simple minded creature, motivated only to feed and reproduce. Lays lots of eggs, make sure it doesn't figure out how tasty its own eggs are. (or itself for that matter.)",
  "PlanktonPhantasmus_name": "Phantasmus",
  "PlanktonPhantasmus_desc": "Is it here or is it there? A creature touched by the great beyond, still, despite its appearance it merely wants company and shelter and will mimic its peers to earn it."
